                            <comment id="13014717" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2011 17:16:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch OutlookRTFStub.patch requires POI 3.8 beta 2, and fetches the RTF message body. It isn&apos;t used though, pending &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-632&quot; title=&quot;Rtf parsing ignores links&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-632&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-632&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014726" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2011 17:35:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OutlookHtmlRtf.patch requires POI 3.8 beta 3, but enables the use of the HTML part in preference to the plain text one&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One thing though - is there a trick to only have the body part of the nested html output when delegating to the Html Parser part way through?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13018302" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 11 Apr 2011 12:46:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Work again 3.8 beta 2 applied in r1091042. Updated patch for POI 3.8 beta 3&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13029755" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 6 May 2011 06:19:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch including &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-656&quot; title=&quot;Outlook dates using the wrong metadata key&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-656&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-656&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
